# Nomvera AI - PRD and Marketing Consistency

Use this rule when editing Nomvera AI landing copy, marketing pages, or PRD-derived content so messaging stays aligned with the product and B2B conversion best practices.

## One-Liner (canonical)

Nomvera AI is a **managed AI training and evaluation firm** that gives frontier model companies access to a **pre-vetted, academically credentialed workforce** - sourced **exclusively from U.S. graduate programs** - **faster and with greater domain fidelity** than any crowdsourced platform can offer.

## Primary persona: Priya (AI Research Lead / Head of Post-Training)

- Manages $8–20M annually for RLHF and evaluation data.
- Decision criteria, in order: (1) verifiable annotator credentials in target domains, (2) consistent output quality without continuous oversight, (3) vendor not serving direct competitors, (4) pricing defensible to VP.

## Secondary persona: Enterprise AI Program Manager

- Large bank, healthcare, or defense contractor; fine-tuning on proprietary workflows.
- Needs: NDA-ready, verifiable credentials, data out of shared annotation pools (isolated project teams).

## Who this is NOT for

- Startups needing 50,000 labeled images at lowest unit price.
- High-volume, low-complexity annotation well-served by automated tooling.
- Any company treating annotation as commodity procurement.

Use a short qualifier in copy where appropriate: e.g. "Built for frontier labs and enterprises - not for commodity, high-volume image annotation."

## Key differentiators (use consistently)

- **Credentials:** Verified U.S. graduate-degree holders, transcript-reviewed; 100% U.S. graduate credentials.
- **Quality:** ≥94% inter-annotator agreement target; calibration before production.
- **Speed:** ≤10 business days to first delivery (in-pool domains).
- **Vendor independence:** Independent; no strategic investment from model developers; no conflict of interest.
- **Data governance:** Isolated project teams; no cross-client data exposure; NDA-ready.

